Neot Golan (Hebrew: נְאוֹת גּוֹלָן‎) is an Israeli settlement and moshav, in the southern Golan Heights, under the administration of Israel. It falls under the jurisdiction of Golan Regional Council, and had a population of 574 in 2016.
The international community considers Israeli settlements in the Golan Heights illegal under international law, but the Israeli government disputes this.


